In April 1994 ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' said that the ''Deluxe'' CD version "adds substantial value to an already excellent game".<ref name="cgw199404">{{Cite magazine |date=April 1994 |title=Invasion Of The Data Stashers |url=http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1994&pub=2&id=117 |url-status=live |magazine=Computer Gaming World |pages=20–42, 33 |access-date=November 10, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111041726/http://www.cgwmuseum.org/galleries/index.php?year=1994&pub=2&id=117 |archive-date=November 11, 2017}}</ref> The San Diego Union said the "'Carmen Sandiego Deluxe' game is challenging, but still fun", adding that "Kids will be anything but bored".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pqarchiver.com/titles?dids=1244220471:1244220471&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jul%2014%252C%201998&author=Jane%20Clifford&pub=The%20San%20Diego%20Union%20-%20Tribune&desc=%2560Carmen%20Sandiego%20Deluxe%2527%20game%20is%20challenging%252C%20but%20still%20lots%20of%20fun&pqatl=google |title=ProQuest Archiver: Titles |access-date=April 20, 2017 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160916044726/http://www.pqarchiver.com/titles?dids=1244220471:1244220471&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jul%2014%252C%201998&author=Jane%20Clifford&pub=The%20San%20Diego%20Union%20-%20Tribune&desc=%2560Carmen%20Sandiego%20Deluxe%2527%20game%20is%20challenging%252C%20but%20still%20lots%20of%20fun&pqatl=google |archive-date=September 16, 2016}}</ref> Boston Globe said it was "for older children".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/290711505.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Nov%2020,%201994&author=Ronald%20Rosenberg,%20Globe%20Staff&pub=Boston%20Globe%20(pre-1997%20Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=&desc=Children's%20educational%20software%20still%20an%20exploding%20market|title=Children's educational software still an exploding market|access-date=July 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304111747/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/boston/doc/290711505.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Nov%2020,%201994&author=Ronald%20Rosenberg,%20Globe%20Staff&pub=Boston%20Globe%20(pre-1997%20Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=&desc=Children's%20educational%20software%20still%20an%20exploding%20market|archive-date=March 4, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Pittsburgh Post-Gazette described it as a "fast paced detective chase".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=sbNRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=jG8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=2965,647651&dq=where%20in%20the%20world%20is%20carmen%20sandiego%20deluxe&hl=en|title=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette - Google News Archive Search|access-date=April 20, 2017|archive-date=October 28, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028204752/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=sbNRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=jG8DAAAAIBAJ&pg=2965,647651&dq=where%20in%20the%20world%20is%20carmen%20sandiego%20deluxe&hl=en|url-status=live}}</ref> The Los Angeles Times said "[Carmen Sandiego's] creators at Broderbund have remade her bigger and badder than ever in a terrific new CD-ROM release of "Where in the World Is Carmen Sandiego? Deluxe Edition", and gave the game a rating of 5 out of 5 stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/doc/281655437.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=May%2030,%201992&author=JEANE%20deCOSTER;%20DAVID%20CROOK&pub=Los%20Angeles%20Times%20(pre-1997%20Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=&desc=Globe-Trotting%20Gangsters|title=Los Angeles Times: Archives - Globe-Trotting Gangsters|access-date=July 7, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111041733/https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/doc/281655437.html?FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=May%2030,%201992&author=JEANE%20deCOSTER;%20DAVID%20CROOK&pub=Los%20Angeles%20Times%20(pre-1997%20Fulltext)&edition=&startpage=&desc=Globe-Trotting%20Gangsters|archive-date=November 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>

